   554	
   555	The dominant sensitivity is not a parameter but a philosophy. Restricting credit to randomized
   556	evidence collapses the median to 9,114 QALYs — dominated by the one lottery-randomized
   557	bucket — while taking every cited effect at face value raises it to 414,264 (Figure 2). That
   558	45-fold range dwarfs the spread from any distributional parameter, and the gap between the
   559	face-value and best-guess estimates is a direct reading of how much of claimed philanthropic
   560	impact rests on evidence that would not survive a causal-inference seminar. The Spearman
   561	tornado (Figure 3) tells the same story within the default stance: the top three drivers are the
   562	global-health allocation share, the realization factor, and global-health credibility.
   563	
   564	5.2 The audit moved the headline by less than 2%
   565	The geography audit is the largest data correction the model has absorbed since publication, and
   566	its effect is small: recentering the allocation on audited service geographies moved the abroad
   567	share from 4.93% to 4.82%, the median from about 205,000 to 201,923, and the blended figure
   568	from about $148,000 to $150,067 per QALY. Both allocations ship with the model, the browser
   569	version exposes them as a version toggle, and the pre-audit parameters remain pinned at tag
   570	v2026.07.20 (audited: v2026.07.22).
