   621	is imputed from a fitted elasticity, not observed. Finally, several anchors rest on a small number
   622	of quasi-experimental papers whose external validity to Scott’s grantees is exactly what the
   623	realization factor is guessing at.
   624	
   625	8 Conclusion
   626	Measured in health, MacKenzie Scott’s $26 billion buys a median of about 202,000 qualityadjusted life-years — several times its cost at the government’s own valuation — and most of that
   627	health comes from the twentieth of her dollars delivered in low-income countries. The number is
   628	a model output under stated priors, not a fact, and the model’s most important output is not
   629	the point estimate but the machinery around it: explicit evidence weights, a 45-fold stance range
   630	that any reader can traverse, versioned corrections, and audits committed as data. Portfolio-scale
   631	philanthropy is measurable in outcomes without waiting for donors to publish outcome data
   632	— their own gift lists, recipients’ tax filings, and the published causal literature suffice — and
   633	the same machinery applies to any large giver. The invitation of the interactive version is the
   634	paper’s real conclusion: disagree with a parameter, move it, and watch what survives.
